26:20.663 --> 26:28.331
It is, as some scholars say, the death of death, which brings us to the actual death of Jesus.

26:30.293 --> 26:39.762
If I can help you recall Mary's deep understanding of what true justice is, the perfect tension of judgment and mercy, we see the justice of God

26:39.874 --> 26:43.758
perfectly on display on the cross of Calvary.

26:44.999 --> 27:08.882
On the cross where Jesus died lies the perfect intersection of God's judgment and his mercy because with Jesus as the perfect one, the holy one, the perfect sacrifice being forsaken by God for the first time in all eternity where that's his judgment on our behalf relinquishes the need for our punishment of sin.

27:09.570 --> 27:16.056
His mercy, perfect judgment and mercy displayed on the cross.

27:18.619 --> 27:19.479
True salvation.

27:21.281 --> 27:25.045
But it is not just the death, resurrection and ascension of Jesus that saves us.

27:26.366 --> 27:34.133
It is the life of Christ that we can look to also for hints and notes and themes of salvation.

27:35.615 --> 27:39.058
Because in the life of Christ, we see the holiness of God lived out

27:40.642 --> 27:49.912
And the life of Jesus, my friends, it is an invitation to a lowly and a spiritually hungry life.

27:51.614 --> 27:58.542
The life of Jesus is an invitation to experience the gospel as we live right now.

27:59.423 --> 28:09.074
It's an invitation to say, hey, the way that you're living right now, if you're addicted to name your drug of choice, if you have an identity issue,

28:09.954 --> 28:20.646
If you're plagued with depression and anxiety and you struggle to find joy in this life, that you place your hope in the other things that this world says, hey, have you tried this out?

28:21.767 --> 28:23.609
You can find happiness and joy in your life.

28:23.729 --> 28:24.990
Have you tired of that life?

28:25.130 --> 28:31.778
The life of Christ invites you to say that there is another way, a better way to live.

28:33.219 --> 28:34.921
And Jesus lives that perfectly.

28:35.221 --> 28:39.666
And all he's saying is that the gospel is not just a golden tick to heaven.

28:40.002 --> 28:46.429
but that you can experience life and life abundantly, as Jesus says, in the here and now.

28:46.970 --> 28:54.679
And the gospel is an invitation to experience that today, not only when you die and stand before God.

28:56.281 --> 29:02.448
The life of Jesus is an invitation to salvation that you can feel and experience and live in now.

29:05.511 --> 29:07.794
Do you feel the tension of needing a savior?

29:10.370 --> 29:15.217
A prevailing idea of our modern mind today is that humanity does not need us, Savior.

29:15.477 --> 29:19.223
In fact, some go so far as to say that, hey, no one's coming.

29:20.965 --> 29:24.931
No one's coming, so go ahead and save yourself through whatever means you see fit.

29:26.213 --> 29:37.970
Do you feel the tension of knowing you are a person full in your humanity and yet acknowledging that there is some dissonance

29:38.178 --> 29:50.998
There's some entropy and chaos, some sort of disruption in the equilibrium of what you think life should be like out there in the world and not just out there, but internally, do you feel that tension?

29:51.839 --> 29:59.090
If that is you today, consider the invitation that Jesus has for you, not just in his death.

29:59.714 --> 30:12.693
not just in his resurrection, not just in the current state after his ascension, but the invitation of Jesus is beautiful and perfect and humble and gentle life that he invites you into.

30:12.713 --> 30:27.154
But remember Mary's words, in order to accept that invitation, it is not to be accepted with a bold and a courageous heart, especially not a strong and proud heart, but it is with

30:27.298 --> 30:34.668
a gentle and a lowly and humble heart that Mary states at the beginning of her song.

30:36.170 --> 30:45.923
Verse 46, and Mary said, my soul magnifies the Lord and my spirit rejoices in God my Savior because he has looked with favor on the humble condition of his servant.

30:47.645 --> 30:57.298
It is the humble, lowly condition of the heart of the self that is required to come and accept the invitation of God of Jesus

30:57.570 --> 30:58.672
and of the Holy Spirit.

31:00.334 --> 31:21.246
Again, if you're here today and you feel that dissonance, you feel that entropy, that chaos around you and inside of you, and you don't know, you've tried all the things out there to resolve that tension, would you consider the way of Jesus and following the way of God?

31:23.449 --> 31:26.514
Again, but to do that, you must

31:27.362 --> 31:29.244
come with a humble heart and posture.

31:30.466 --> 31:32.468
Mary acknowledges, and we'll close with this.

31:33.149 --> 31:39.996
Mary acknowledges that she needs a savior and concludes that God is the savior.

31:40.977 --> 31:45.903
But in her acknowledgement of needing a savior, she is not dismayed over that reality.

31:45.963 --> 31:46.904
Let me make that very clear.

31:47.204 --> 31:50.368
She acknowledges that she needs a savior.

31:50.528 --> 31:55.634
Very counter to what our modern day way of thinking is like.

31:55.938 --> 32:02.788
She acknowledges that she needs a savior, but she's not dismayed over that reality.

32:03.408 --> 32:05.151
In fact, what does she say?

32:05.211 --> 32:12.962
Her soul magnifies the Lord and her spirit rejoices.

32:13.943 --> 32:14.244
Why?

32:14.284 --> 32:24.498
Because she understands that the God of Abraham is the perfect savior because he is perfectly just in his judgment and his mercy and his holy

32:25.730 --> 32:29.254
And through that she knows he is so trustworthy.

32:30.535 --> 32:41.186
He is so trustworthy that she can place her hope that he will be faithful to the covenant promise that he made to her forefather Abraham.

32:45.010 --> 32:52.498
Would you be able to consider the way that Mary sees her need of a savior for your life today?

32:53.762 --> 32:57.085
We'll wrap up with this one of our dear friends, Colleen Davenport.

32:57.626 --> 33:01.149
Over in our Rive Kids team, she wrote this in her teaching to our kids.

33:01.630 --> 33:03.972
And let me just kind of step to the side here and say this.

33:04.313 --> 33:09.938
We have some of these best, if not the best curriculum writers for our kids ministry.

33:10.839 --> 33:11.520
Absolutely.

33:12.220 --> 33:13.622
That is 100% facts.

33:13.642 --> 33:15.644
10 out of 10 would recommend.

33:17.346 --> 33:21.810
This is what Colleen writes and wrote for what the kids are learning today.

33:23.298 --> 33:30.164
And I think it sums up God's heart a saver toward his people and towards those who would be humble enough to submit to him.

33:30.204 --> 33:43.817
And for our church family here, Riverview, as a family of God's people, we must reflect who God is in the people that we are becoming.

33:46.400 --> 33:51.965
And Colleen Synthesis of who God is and what he does according to Mary is spot on and will end with this quote.

33:52.065 --> 33:53.266
She wrote right to this.

33:53.826 --> 33:55.488
He shows mercy to families.

33:56.589 --> 33:59.232
He lifts up people who are not considered important.

34:00.093 --> 34:01.494
He fills those who are hungry.

34:01.534 --> 34:03.136
He helps his people.

34:04.738 --> 34:10.284
And he is kind and remembers his people.

34:10.304 --> 34:15.690
Let me pray that over us as we consider God as our Savior.

34:16.991 --> 34:18.173
To become like him.

34:18.213 --> 34:23.058
To care for those who are lowly and on the margins.

34:25.794 --> 34:27.977
to help his people and to remember his people.

34:28.838 --> 34:32.042
Let me pray that for our church and we'll wrap up our time.

34:38.429 --> 34:41.513
Lord, what a difficult thing.

34:43.455 --> 34:52.466
Because there's so many voices out there, Lord, that would lead us to be angry, to be divisive, to make it about us versus then.

34:54.306 --> 35:05.505
to say that we are the ones who are righteous and holy and saved and taken away from the crazy chaos of this world, and you guys can just live in your own way.

35:05.565 --> 35:08.329
Lord, may that be so far from our church family.

35:10.092 --> 35:20.850
Lord, may we exemplify with excellence, with humility and gentleness, Lord, the heart posture that we carried

35:21.122 --> 35:47.826
when we first encountered and experienced the gospel of Jesus Christ, and that is one of humility and gentleness and neediness and dependence, may we echo and reflect Lord, the love and the care and the mercy you have, the people who are not seen in society, those who are on the margins, the ostracized,

35:48.162 --> 35:50.044
The quote unquote, losers of society.

35:50.064 --> 36:04.980
Whatever that means, I pray that Lord, you would move our hearts, Lord, to see those that the world would throw away because you saw us, Lord, in our sin, and yet you shined your mercy and your love on us.

36:06.041 --> 36:09.665
May our church become people like that, Lord.

36:11.207 --> 36:17.554
May Lansing know that Riverview is a church that is for the community

36:18.210 --> 36:32.071
that is for the hurting, that this place is a home for those who just don't have it altogether, and that they would meet and encounter the living God, the Savior of the world.

36:33.032 --> 36:43.127
We thank you for Mary's theological insights, her love of scripture to just know it so that we may understand more of your heart for us, Lord.

36:44.650 --> 36:47.474
We thank you for Christ, all that he has done.

36:48.130 --> 36:49.938
We pray this in your Son's name, amen.

